title: Honduras Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: Consumer Price Index CPI in Honduras increased to 399.20 points in October from 396.60 points in September of 2022. Consumer Price Index CPI in Honduras averaged 188.20 points from 1992 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 399.20 points in October of 2022 and a record low of 28.10 points in January of 1992. In Honduras, the Consumer Price Index or CPI measures changes in the prices paid by consumers for a basket of goods and services. This page provides - Honduras Consumer Price Index (CPI) - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Banco Central De Honduras
